# Git Workflow Standards

Follow these conventions when performing git operations.

## When This Applies

- Creating commits
- Opening pull requests
- Code reviews
- Branch management

## Commit Conventions

All commits MUST follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/):

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

### Commit Types

| Type       | Use For            |
| ---------- | ------------------ |
| `feat`     | New features       |
| `fix`      | Bug fixes          |
| `docs`     | Documentation      |
| `style`    | Formatting         |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring |
| `perf`     | Performance        |
| `test`     | Tests              |
| `chore`    | Maintenance        |
| `build`    | Build changes      |
| `ci`       | CI/CD changes      |

### Project Scopes

Define project-specific scopes in your `AGENTS.md` file. Common examples:

- `api` - Backend API
- `ui` - Frontend UI
- `db` - Database
- `auth` - Authentication
- `build` - Build config
- `cursor` - Cursor/agent workflow

### Docs vs Agentic Workflow

- `docs:` - Traditional documentation (README, API docs)
- `chore(cursor):` - Cursor commands, rules, agent plans
- `docs(cursor):` - Cursor reference documentation

## Branch Workflow

1. **Default:** personal dev branches (e.g. `ryan`, `colin`) — no issue id required in the name when every commit footers the issue (`Refs`, `Closes`, etc.). Agents enforce this via [`/git/commit`](../commands/git/commit.md) and [linear-traceability.mdc](./linear-traceability.mdc).
2. **Optional:** `<firstname>/<issue-id>-<short-slug>` when you want Linear obvious in `git` output or long-lived isolation.
3. Rebase onto `main` (never merge)
4. Use `--force-with-lease` when pushing after rebase

## PR Review Prefixes

| Prefix      | Meaning           | Blocking |
| ----------- | ----------------- | -------- |
| `major:`    | Must fix          | Yes      |
| `minor:`    | Should fix        | No       |
| `nit:`      | Tiny improvement  | No       |
| `question:` | Clarification     | No       |
| `praise:`   | Positive feedback | No       |

## Issue Tracker Integration

Configure your issue tracker details in `AGENTS.md`. Magic words typically auto-close issues on merge:

- `Closes {PREFIX}-XXX` / `Fixes {PREFIX}-XXX` / `Resolves {PREFIX}-XXX`
- Use `Refs {PREFIX}-XXX` to link without closing
- Do not require issue IDs in branch names; link issues via commit footer (and optionally `defaultLinearIssue` in `AGENTS.md`).

**Optional default for personal branches** (repo root `AGENTS.md`):

```text
defaultLinearIssue: N43-123
```

Agents use this when the branch name has no issue id (see `/git/commit` Step 1b).

Examples:

- Linear: branch `ryan` with `Closes N43-123` or `Refs N43-123`; or branch `ryan/n43-123-add-auth`
- Jira: `Closes PROJ-456`, branch `erik` or `ryan/proj-456-fix-bug`
- GitHub Issues: `Closes #789`, branch `ryan` or `ryan/789-update-docs`

